FBIS3-41596 "jpten004___94066" JPRS-TEN-94-004 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Environmental Issues 17 February 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA REGIONAL AFFAIRS Arab-Israeli Environment Talks First Practical Breakthrough Reported at Environment Talks TA1611060893 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 16 Nov 93 TA1611060893 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] There has been a first practical breakthrough in the multilateral talks on environmental issues. A joint Jordanian-Israeli mechanism was established at the Cairo conference in order to deal with sea pollution in al-'Aqabah and to protect the gulf's coral reefs. Our correspondent Shulamit Schmerling reports that the other delegations participating in the talks, including the World Bank, agreed to help finance the joint mechanism.
